<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 04 at 7:32AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A band of heavy snow will impact the area this morning...
A band of snow along a strong cold front will bring a period of
heavy snow to parts of Southwestern Montana this morning,
including areas along I-90.
While this band of snow will not last long in any one location,
generally 30 minutes to an hour, a quick inch of snow will be
possible along with reductions in visibility to a quarter mile.
If traveling this morning, give yourself extra time to reach your
destination, and use your headlights to make yourself more
visible to other motorists.</description>
